CONGRATULATIONS FOR THE BABY!!!!

For the problems with Roxie and the baby here is some advice:

Try teaching Roxie that hurting her/ him is bad like if she is nice next to like a doll give her a treat. If she attacks the doll don‚Äôt. Try kinda like to  make Roxie think the doll is like pulling her tail( try pets and maybe small tugs to the ear if she is sensitive to pulling her tail) . When introducing Roxie to the baby give her like a sleeping pill or calming pill. Make sure she isn‚Äôt agitated by anything else in the previous hour( maybe more) . Try teaching the baby not to pull her tail like use a toy cat to teach her try kinda like to pretend the toy cat is hurt by pulling its tail. When around Roxie give her/ him something to hold on to because of her/ his reflex to grab stuff. Hope with was helpful.

We as the TFG community would like permission to call the baby TFB( The Frustrated Baby) .
